> The correct tap is an 8mm x 1.25 STI. STI is an abbreviation for
> Standard Thread Insert. A better solution, if you have the 'meat' for it
> is to use a Timesert or Keensert.

I agree, though it is intresting to note that the new Mexican engines come
with helicoils in all three mustache bar holes from the factory.  They
work fine if correctly applied and may be better for deep hole
applications.  Do the Tim/Keenserts come in deep versions?

